caption: There are so many flavors to choose from and the taste is totally delicious, so good I had to go back again. The best ice cream in town, great service, lots of flavors, something for all and the price is low for what you get!

Great little ice cream shop downtown that just reopened. They only had a few flavors because of this, but the ice cream was fresh and delicious. We also got a little bag of popcorn which had the perfect movie butter flavor. Will definitely go back.

Hi Jeni, I want to express my gratitude. Since you became owner of my FAVORITE popcorn shop, you have been amazing. San Diego this is hands down the BEST POPCORN in town!!! Jeni customer service is the bomb show your support you won't be disappoint....
Had a friend come into town and she asked me to take her here again. The bill was decent for the quality. They have so many great reviews for a reason.

We drove downtown and paid for parking to find a hand written note on the door that they were closed for the week. We went at 1PM on Saturday which is a listed business hour.  It would have been nice if they would have updated their site, …

Mochilato is one of my favorite desserts - soft and squishy rice cakes filled with delicious and creamy gelato ice cream. I used to buy boxes and boxes of them from trader joes or 99 ranch and finish them by the time I got to the parking lot.
Do not leave if it's busy, it is worth it. The service here is above par.

Great place. Nice people. A lot of variety. But needs to be a little faster got the Oreo and I got the Nutella filling. Was great choice. I actually will try something fruity next time because it looks amazing.
Great ambiance & decor. I'll return with my relatives. This place has a nice atmosphere. Food and feeling reminds me of Kansas City.
Got there about one, it wasn't busy. I had a brother come into town and he asked me to go back here. The bill was well within reason for the quality.
Food was so yummy. The service here is above par. Prices are fair I would say. I can see why they have a lot of good reviews.
Stopped in on a Monday I think. Service is typically great. Ambience reminds me of Colorado Springs area.

Stopped by on a whim and got some ice cream... So Yummy! Mixed Berry and the Abuelita got chocolate flavors are a must. The woman serving us was very kind and super helpful. Definitely going to keep it on my list of places to visit while in San Diego.
This location is one of my favorites. Fast and courteous service. The place has an awesome atmosphere.
Definitely one of the best places in the area. I'll return with my friends. Bring your appetite because portions are generous. Feels like a place in Los Angeles I loved.

Their ice cream is hand made, everything about the store is a local mom & pop. It's absolutely wonderful, magical and a great treat for the entire family. Would highly recommend to anyone in the area looking for ice cream.
Food was so tasty. The staff was friendly and observant. Prices were fair for the quality of the food. This place has great reviews for a reason.
came in on a thurs. there was fast and courteous service. atmosphere is like a restaurant in fort worth i loved.

The best ice cream I have ever had. The chocolate sorbet has such a strong chocolate flavor, they really managed to turn a chocolate bar into a frozen dessert so well. Also, the mint ice cream is incredibly fresh tasting. It's very clear …

I tried the Hibiscus Lime sorbet and that was good but I had to get the apple pie flavor. I just love anything apple pie. The smidge scoop was perfect for an after dinner dessert. It costs $2.50 for that scoop, which isn't too bad! The ice …
Jessica was amazing and friendly. Especially with my son who has autism.
Visited here for the first time ever after they reopened. Absolutely loved the popcorn (and the prices)!

Hadn't been here in a few years as a local.  Staying across the street overnight and had a taste for a snack of popcorn during the early afternoon. Got a bag of both the movie style and caramel/cheese combo. So disappointed. Both were extremely stale. Definitely not popped daily.
Best icecream ive ever tasted great texture

Great ice cream spot close to the ballpark.  Toppings are mixed in to the ice cream on a cold stone and the scoops are humongous.  Get a regular or child size unless you are sharing.  Also has popcorn and hotdogs you can bring into the ballpark, but didn't try those

My kids and I just stopped by and tried this place after school was out today and absolutely love it. The prices are low, there was upfront parking and the ice cream was so delicious and creamy. We had strawberry, coffee, orange cream, double dark chocolate, sweet cream, pure vanilla and Nutella. All flavors were phenomenal.
Biggest ice cream sandwich ever!!
Really good cinnamon ice cream
Yummy yummy yummy! The amaretto ice cream was tasty and creamy!  The coffee ice cream was delectable!  The staff was awesome, also!
Nice spot to stop following a game. Great customer service and flavors were solid. I suggest eating there, if on the go get plenty napkins.
Delicious.
Decent ice cream. Glad to support local. Quiet neighborhood. Tons of seating.
Food was super flavorful. Looking forward to returning with my friends. Prices were average for the menu.
Great ice cream and good sized portions for the price. Got a double scoop with dipped cone and it really filled me up...
Only had ice cream it was really good. Except messy. Dripped on my damn shirt. Drat. It was worth it tho.

The icecream and the popcorn was good, but they could have done a better job with the cookies. The cookies had a strange taste, and it was mostly tasteless. I understand that their specialty is popcorn, but they could’ve done better. I would recommend the icecream though.

Awesome store and great service! Ice cream is homemade and delicious!  Hot dogs were great.  Nice little store in Downtown.  If you’re not trying to spend $30 a person or just need a quick snack this is your place. Highly recommend.  We need more mom and pop shops like this! Couldn’t be happier.

Ice cream is homemade and mixed in as your order. They have a lot of variety and the portions are relatively bigger for the price. The ice cream cookie sandwich has about three scoops worth of ice cream, definitely sharing size!
Great ice cream and flavored popcorn :)
The caramel corn is some of the best caramel corn I’ve ever had. The “movie theater” butter popcorn was chewy and had no salt.  Staff was friendly and welcoming.
Great cones, great flavors, close to the action (and conference center). Worth the stop if you’re looking for quick ice cream!
Love this place great owners
i like it here, excellent food & service. the service was helpful and kind. they have so many reviews for a reason.
Home made ice cream.  Great flavors and worth the price.  It's a classic ice cream shop.  Recommended

Cute little place in the heart of noisy CA , I never knew that lavender ice cream could taste so good !  I took two cones with two scoops and even wanted more ! It was so Delish !!!They make their own waffles in spot , it's crispy and yummier . I loved all flavors but the lavender the most . It's a must try !!!
Great prices for great food
Really good cookies. Well curated selection of ice cream sandwiches. Heat sealed bags slightly difficult to open.
Great ice cream and lots of different flavors.
Great place to relax, people watch, eat good food or all the above.  The staff was very friendly and kind. The prices are fair for the quality of food. Makes me feel like I in Nashville again.

Ice cream had a piece of hair in it which was unfortunate. Cheddar popcorn packed cheese powder but lacked pow. Kettle corn didn’t deliever as much as I had hoped either. Sorry to say I will not be returning.

This I'd a wonderful family owned business! I will definitely be ordering flavored popcorn from here again! The owner is the sweetest person ever! The flavors are amazingly exactly like the real thing!
I love there popcorn. I Love the menu too because it's set up like ur at a restaurant waiting to order food!  Very delicious!
I absolutely love this place!!!!!! Awesome popcorn and GREAT customer service. I will recommend this place to anyone. I promise you will enjoy the different flavors of popcorn.
Great service. OK ice cream.
Only tried the ice cream and found it to be acceptable but not the best I've ever had

Amazing homemade ice cream! I've been to over 50 ice cream shops all over the US and this shop is among the BEST!  Between my husband and I, we sampled 6 flavors and the owner was so friendly and patient! All of the flavors were really good …
Yum
Really nice mom n pop shop.

When googled too ice cream places, this showed up. So my family and I walked there from cafe sevilla (delicious Spanish tapas). I went for a cone and left with the biggest most delicious cookies sandwich I have ever eaten. I don't what …
Delicious ice cream peanut butter
The banana ice cream was yummy! Lots to choose from, super friendly!
fantastic ice cream and well worth a visit..  hit it after a padre game or before..whatever..
I found a hair in my ice cream but got anything i wanted for free.
Good ice cream!
I thought the price was amazing, the ice cream was to die for.... And the people were so sweet!! What an amazing experience!
Wonderful service

The kettle corn was sub par and largely overpriced. The cookies were cakey. The ice cream was good and the service was good. Overall, I will not be returning.  Edit: my order consisted of the kettle corn, and the ice cream sandwich was the cookies and cream with a chocolate cookie on top.
My family loved the ice cream so much we visited twice before ending our vacation.
Very good ice cream a little pricey but worth the price
Do not eat the hot dogs they will give you diarrhia
Gross smell, we ordered anyway and shouldn't have. Blackberry ice cream was inedible, threw it away. My child had chocolate chip cookie sandwich and it was disgusting too.
Their ice cream is really good! Amaretto is my favorite.
Kids and I had a great time.
I'm not sure who the dude was that was working tonight but he made a killer milk shake!

My girlfriend and I went in for a hot dog and some ice cream and ended up meeting Kim, yes, THE Kim. She, along with the other young lady behind the counter, were super friendly and we ended up chatting for quite some time. It was an awesome experience in regards to the food and the hospitality. Will definitely return.
Great staff great ice cream!  They also sell great popcorn great for gifts and great for eating. Over all this place is.... GREAT
Delicious food. Awesome folks. David... You rock. Thanks for your hospitality.
Very good the guy always so friendly and kind his popcorn the best been taking my daughter since she was little :)) love coming here
Love this place! Peanut butter with graham cracker crumbs for me, double dark chocolate with Heath bar and strawberries for wifey.
Amazing. This place has cheap hot dogs and amazing homemade ice cream. Perfect for twitchcon attendees.
2 nathans hot dogs for $5 in the heart of downtown SD. Best deal around ! The ice cream is great to
Great Dogs and Drink combo. Close to the ballpark.

Wonderfully delicious homemade ice cream. Even the other dessert items they served (smoothies, ice cream sandwiches, homemade cookies) looked delicious. The service was also great, everyone was kind. Definitely recommend it.
The best ice cream!!!
Friendly service, amazing ice cream!

Had the absolute pleasure of having them provide the best popcorn treats for my wedding. Presentation was incredible as well as the freshness and taste. We make specific trips to the shop to satisfy our cravings for sweets.
For a quick hot dog it's hard to beat the value. 2 dogs and a canned beverage for $5! Quick, great service, and lots of ice cream and popcorn options for additional snacks.

My husband and I were visiting San Diego and wanted something for dessert after dinner.  The guy inside was really helpful and nice.  He even gave us a little gift after we told him we were visiting San Diego for our honeymoon. The ice …

Great little spot for a snack or treat.  We stopped in for their homemade ice cream, which was delicious.  My husband had a homemade ice cream sandwich which was so big he couldn't finish it.  Share one with a friend!  Service was very friendly, I would definitely go again.
Yummy ice cream sandwiches

Heard a lot about this place so I decided to try it...their signature flavor Salted Caramel was too sweet for me, so I opted for the Sobert Caught in the Rain...nice and fruity....It was not bad...  But Just OK...

The ice cream was decent but quite generic (strawberry, vanilla, chocolate, coffee and etc...).  There's not much to set their ice cream apart from something you can find at a grocery store for much less money.  I had the ice cream sandwich …

Love their ice cream! It was absolutely delicious! However, there are A LOT of baby strollers that get jammed into this place with screaming children. So as long as you're ready for that, you'll be fine.Also, please be mindful of sampling. Salted caramel tastes like salted caramel.

CrunchTime the best ice cream, ever! The staff is great, always good jams playing, and they've got outdoor seating too.Nonna D's Oatmeal is my absolute favorite. Other great ones to try Sweet as Honey and Odey Gooey Butter cake.Well worth the wait, I promise!

This place is a little pricey for ice cream but it is worth the price tag. The ingredients are organic, fresh and the final product, a delicious cold treat that you will surely make return visits for. The staff is friendly, personable and …
CG Fi
Great icecream ! The cookies are excellent as well
Very nice gent behind the counter.    Very small....a bit expensive!   Taste them before you buy as some are better than others!

Hole in the wall atmosphere.   Went for ice cream only. We were told their ice cream machine cannot handle chunky things so all of their flavors are smooth. Even mint chocolate chip and butter pecan ( which actually tastes more like cinnamon)!  Sloppy large portions make you realize that the ice cream is pretty bland.
We enjoyed the ice cream sandwiches and popcorn.  Owner was very nice and went out of her making it a pleasant experience.
Great Chicago style hot dogs!  The owner Kim is very passionate about their food.  Great place!
